m:properties.d:SpeakerDescription: Sanjay Soni is a Sr. Technical Product Marketing Manager in the SQL Server Business Intelligence and Data Warehousing Marketing team at Microsoft. Previous Microsoft roles include Business Intelligence Evangelist, responsible for enabling self-service BI to 40,000+ users at Microsoft. Sanjay is know for his passion, enthusiasm, driving structure, and delivering results for customers in the BI and Data Warehousing area during last 15 years of diversified experiences. He is an MCDBA, MCTS and specializes in Business Intelligence using MS technologies including Power BI, Analysis Services, Reporting Services, SharePoint BI, PDW etc. Sanjay has authored and presented a variety of papers and sessions in last 15 years at various BI conferences including Tech-Ed, BI Conference, PASS, SQL Connections, SharePoint Conference, and TDWI.

Jen Underwood is a Senior Director at DataRobot. Over the past 20 years, Jen has held worldwide product management roles at Microsoft and served as a technical lead for system implementation firms. She has a unique blend of product management and “hands-on” experience in data warehousing, reporting, visualization, and advanced analytics. In addition to keeping a constant pulse on industry trends, she enjoys digging into oceans of data to solve complex problems with machine learning.
Jen has a Bachelor of Business Administration – Marketing, Cum Laude from the University of Wisconsin, Milwaukee and a post-graduate certificate in Computer Science – Data Mining from the University of California, San Diego.

Scott Shaw has over a decade of experience in data management. He is a frequent speaker at local and national community events and has co-authored two books on T-SQL. He teaches as well as implements Pig, Hive, Hadoop, as well as teaches courses on SQL Server, and Microsoft BI. He is currently working on a book titled "Practical Hive” to be published by Apress publishing. He lives in St. Louis and is a Sr. Solutions Engineer for Hortonworks.

Ike Ellis is a Senior Data Architect and partner for Crafting Bytes. He has designed and implemented data solutions for many well-known organizations. He has been a Microsoft Data Platform MVP since 2011. He co-authored the book "Developing Azure Solutions," now in its second edition. He is a popular speaker at SQLBits, PASS Summit, and SQL in the City. He speaks at user groups, code camps, and SQLSaturdays. He has written courses on SQL Server for developers, Power BI, SSRS, SSIS, and SSAS for Wintellect. He has an upcoming course on CosmosDB. He founded the San Diego Tech Immersion Group, a technical book club based in San Diego and is the co-chair of the San Diego Software Architecture Group.

Marco is a Business Intelligence consultant and mentor. He wrote several books about Power BI, Analysis Service, and Power Pivot. He also regularly writes articles and white papers that are available on sqlbi.com. Marco is a Microsoft MVP and an SSAS Maestro, the highest level of certification on Microsoft Analysis Services. Today, Marco focuses his time with SQLBI customers, traveling extensively to train and consult on DAX and data modeling for Power BI and Analysis Services. Marco also teaches public classes worldwide. Marco is a regular speaker at international conferences like Microsoft Ignite, PASS Summit, and SQLBits. He also enjoys delivering evening sessions at local user groups during his trips.

He also regularly writes articles and white papers that are available on sqlbi.com. Marco is a Microsoft MVP and an SSAS Maestro, the highest level of certification on Microsoft Analysis Services. Today, Marco focuses his time with SQLBI customers, traveling extensively to train and consult on DAX and data modeling for Power BI and Analysis Services. Marco also teaches public classes worldwide. Marco is a regular speaker at international conferences like Microsoft Ignite, PASS Summit, and SQLBits. He also enjoys delivering evening sessions at local user groups during his trips.

Rob Collie is President and Founder of PowerPivotPro, a national consulting firm 100% dedicated to Power BI and the “Agile BI” methodology. A former engineering leader at Microsoft, Rob led the BI-focused team within Microsoft Excel, and later shaped Power Pivot v1 – the groundbreaking forerunner to Power BI. He is a sought-after speaker with a distinctive, down-to-earth style, and author of the world’s #1-selling Power BI book.

A former engineering leader at Microsoft, Rob led the BI-focused team within Microsoft Excel, and later shaped Power Pivot v1 – the groundbreaking forerunner to Power BI. He is a sought-after speaker with a distinctive, down-to-earth style, and author of the world’s #1-selling Power BI book.

Chris Webb is a member of the Power BI CAT team. He is the author of "Power Query for Power BI and Excel" and a co-author of "SQL Server Analysis Services 2012: The BISM Tabular Model", "Expert Cube Development with SQL Server 2008 Analysis Services", and "MDX Solutions with Microsoft SQL Server Analysis Services 2005 and Hyperion Essbase".

Jen Stirrup, Microsoft Regional Director and MVP is a well-known Business Intelligence and Data Visualization expert, author, data strategist, and Master of Business Administration (MBA) student in London. Jen leads a boutique analytics consultancy, delivering strategic advice to companies large and small.
Jen has presented in Africa, India, Europe and North America. Jen has presented at Ignite, Techorama, TechEd, PASS Summit, SQLBits, and SQLSaturday events in Europe and the US. She also delivers the MAPA Azure Architects course worldwide with Microsoft team members. Jen was also featured on the Best of PASS Summit 2015 DVD as one of the top 10 speakers. Jen also was awarded PASS prestigious PASSion Award in 2012

Andrew Brust is Senior Director, Technical Product Marketing and Evangelism at Datameer (http://www.datameer.com) and writes a blog for ZDNet called "Big on Data" (http://www.zdnet.com/blog/big-data). Andrew is co-author of "Programming Microsoft SQL Server 2012" (Microsoft Press); an advisor to NYTECH, the New York Technology Council; serves as Microsoft Regional Director and MVP; and writes the Redmond Review column for VisualStudioMagazine.com.

Kasper de Jonge is a Program Manager on the SQL Server Analysis Services team, based out of Redmond, WA. With more than 5 years of experience as a developer and consultant on data warehousing solutions using all products from the Microsoft BI stack, Kasper has worked on everything from corporate intranets using SharePoint and Analysis Services to near real-time reporting in the cloud. He has presented at many technical conferences, including PASS Summit and SQLSaturday. You can read Kasper’s blog at http://www.powerpivotblog.nl.

Paco Gonzalez is the CEO of SolidQ North America, and a Microsoft Data Platform MVP. Focused on Business Analytics and Artificial Intelligence, he specializes in helping organizations become data driven from a strategic and technical perspective. Paco is a speaker at small and large conferences such as PASS Summit, Ignite, and Business Applications Summit, and he has published several books and whitepapers. He is based in Atlanta, GA.

Paco Gonzalez is the CEO of SolidQ North America, and a Microsoft Data Platform MVP. Focused on Business Analytics and Artificial Intelligence, he specializes in helping organizations become data driven from a strategic and technical perspective. Paco is a speaker at small and large conferences such as PASS Summit, Ignite, and Business Applications Summit, and he has published several books and whitepapers. He is based in Atlanta, GA.

Miguel is a Program Manager at Microsoft, working on Power Query since Day 1 of the project. Miguel is in charge of creating data discovery, import and transformation experiences that delight Information Workers and other BI users, as well as driving Community and Customer engagements for Power Query.
While Miguel is directly responsible for most of the painful experiences in Power Query today, he is also committed to listening every customer's feedback to improve the product.

Lynn Langit is a Cloud and Big Data Architect. She's been working with a team on an AWS IoT project this year. Lynn speaks, blogs and creates courses on technical topics for LinkedIn/Lynda.com.
She holds a number of partner awards - Microsoft MVP for Data Platform, AWS Community Hero, Google Developer Expert (Cloud). Her blog is at www.LynnLangit.com. She is also director of the non-profit Teaching Kids Programming (www.TeachingKidsProgramming.org).

Lynn Langit is a Cloud and Big Data Architect. She's been working with a team on an AWS IoT project this year. Lynn speaks, blogs and creates courses on technical topics for LinkedIn/Lynda.com.
She holds a number of partner awards - Microsoft MVP for Data Platform, AWS Community Hero, Google Developer Expert (Cloud). Her blog is at www.LynnLangit.com. She is also director of the non-profit Teaching Kids Programming (www.TeachingKidsProgramming.org).

Michelle Ufford leads centralized solutions for Data Engineering & Analytics at Netflix, where she’s focused on making it easier to develop & manage complex, high-value datasets. Previously, she led the Data Management team at GoDaddy, where she architected data engineering solutions supporting real-time personalization and helped pioneer Hadoop data warehousing techniques. She’s also a published author, award-winning open-source contributor, Most Valuable Professional (MVP) for Microsoft Data Platform, and well-known influencer in the data community.

Hyoun Park is the Chief Research Officer of Blue Hill Research where he oversees day-to-day research operations, delivery and methodology focused on vendor and technology selection. In addition, Park covers analytics and enterprise mobility technologies as a noted advisor, social influencer, and practitioner. Park has been named as a top 10 Big Data, analytics, and mobility influencer including quotes in USA Today, the Los Angeles Times, and a wide variety of industry media sources.

Marc Reguera, an 18-year Microsoft veteran, leads the Finance teams in Services (for Customer Services and Support and Premier). Marc drives the revenue planning and analysis for the US sales organization and more recently optimized Microsoft spending in R&D and Marketing for the Server and Tools Division. He has also taught classes on data visualization and business storytelling to over 3,000 finance employees in the last 4 years and regularly meets with customers to showcase Microsoft BI capabilities.

I am an independent consultant based in the UK, specializing in all things Excel, especially delivering BI within Excel.
I came to appreciate the power and versatility of Excel as an enterprise tool in the mid-90s when managing the delivery of a data warehouse project.
Now a freelance consultant, I specialize in Excel automation and BI delivered via Excel. An 11 year veteran of Microsoft's MVP program, my life mission is to persuade small and medium corporates that data analysis and BI is important to them too, and that Power BI can help then find that information, in a straight-forward and cost-effective manner.

Sandy Rivas is a Program Manager for Power BI at Microsoft. A 17+ year Microsoft veteran, she has shipped numerous Microsoft products. She manages the Power BI online Community and Power BI User Groups across the world. Her real-world use of Power BI with her brother’s business has given her a keen insight to the practical uses and value of self-service BI. Sandy has a passion for empowering customers to master their data through self-service BI. Her practical experience & enthusiasm is contagious!

Theresa Palmer is a Program Manager in the Microsoft SQL Server Information Services Group. She is currently working on Microsoft Power Query for Excel, which offers end user experiences around data discovery, data consumption, and data mashups.

David Smith is the R Community Lead at Microsoft. With a background in data science, he writes daily about applications of predictive analytics at the Revolutions blog (blog.revolutionanalytics.com), and is a co-author of “Introduction to R”, the R manual. Follow David on Twitter as @revodavid.

Miguel is a Sr. Program Manager for Power BI at Microsoft in charge of real-time experiences. Chilean, amateur musician, soccer and (very recent) ice hockey player, entertainment and data frenetic fan. Previous experience in transport, tourism, retail and tech industries. Miguel holds Industrial and Electrical Engineering degrees, and an MBA from Berkeley-Haas 2011.

Chandoo has one goal in life: "to make you awesome in Excel". With this mission, he started Chandoo.org, an Excel blog & community, in early 2008 to share tips, tutorials and downloads with the world. He is passionate about data analytics and visualization. He is a six-time consecutive winner of the MVP award from Microsoft for his contributions to the Excel community (2009-2014).
To learn more about Chandoo or become awesome in Excel, please visit http://chandoo.org/wp/

James is the CEO and a Principal Consultant of Decision Management Solutions. He is the leading expert in how to use business rules and analytic technology to build Decision Management Systems. James is passionate about using Decision Management Systems to help companies improve decision making and develop an agile, analytic and adaptive business. He provides strategic consulting to companies of all sizes, working with clients in all sectors to adopt decision making technology. James has spent the last 20 years developing approaches, tools, and platforms that others can use to build more effective information systems. He has led Decision Management efforts for leading companies in insurance, banking, health management and telecommunications.

Jordan Goldmeier is an internationally recognized spreadsheet and data visualization expert, author, producer, and Excel MVP. He is the owner of Cambia Factor data consulting agency and the author of Advanced Excel Essentials. Jordan challenges companies to rethink how they use their data by focusing on returning value rather than acquiring and implementing new technology. He has consulted with and provided training for the North American Treaty Alliance, the United States Air Force and Navy, the Pentagon, the University of Cincinnati, Financial Times, and others.

Dan Fylstra is founder and President of Frontline Systems Inc., an analytics software developer and marketer active in the Microsoft ecosystem for 25 years. Frontline’s software for Excel complements the Power BI suite and supports the full range of advanced analytics.
Prior to founding Frontline Systems, Dan was a serial entrepreneur who co-founded several software companies and a biotech venture.

James G Kobielus is an industry veteran. He serves as IBM's big data evangelist; as senior program director for product marketing in big data analytics, and as editor-in-chief of IBM Data Magazine. Kobielus spearheads IBM's thought leadership activities in Big Data, Hadoop, cognitive computing, enterprise data warehousing, and advanced analytics. He advises IBM's product management and marketing teams in all things big data. He has spoken at leading industry events & has published several books.

Dr. Mahesh Kumar is the CEO of Tiger Analytics and has over 13 years of Data Analytics experience. He has conducted extensive research on Data Mining and Statistical Modeling to solve problems related to forecasting, pricing, promotions etc. and has extensive consulting experience with companies like McKinsey & Company, SAS, JC Penney, Levis, TTX etc. Dr. Kumar was previously on the faculty of Smith School of Business and Rutgers Business School.

Dean Abbott is Co-Founder and Chief Data Scientist of SmarterHQ. Mr. Abbott is an internationally recognized data mining and predictive analytics expert with three decades of experience applying advanced data mining algorithms, data preparation techniques, and data visualization methods to real-world problems, including customer analytics, fraud detection, risk modeling, text mining, survey analysis, planned giving, and many more.
Mr. Abbott is the author of Applied Predictive Analytics (Wiley, 2014) and co-author of IBM SPSS Modeler Cookbook (Packt Publishing, 2013). He is a highly-regarded and popular speaker at Predictive Analytics and Data Mining conferences worldwide, and is on the Advisory Boards for the UC/Irvine Predictive Analytics Certificate as well as the UCSD Data Mining Certificate programs.
He holds a B.S. in Mathematics of Computation from Rensselaer (1985) and a Master of Applied Mathematics from the University of Virginia (1987)

Oz du Soleil is an Excel developer, blogger, trainer, co-host of ExcelTV, raconteur and newly recognized Excel MVP. He and his blog are known for a colorful and fierce commitment to empowering people who don’t have an IT team or the skillset to manage their own data.
Oz is also lead author of the forthcoming book, Guerrilla Data Analysis 2nd Ed., co-written with Mr. Excel, Bill Jelen. He recently relocated to Portland, OR and is known for his passion for ghost pepper sriracha.

Richard is an Executive Consultant, Board Advisory & Senior Thought Leader at IMECS, LLC, a management consulting firm. He specializes in the domains of Privacy, Analytics, Digital Transformation & Strategic Leadership.
He is the Author of “The Data Leadership Nexus”, a strategic framework for transforming Organizations’ into Predictive Enterprises. Richard works with CEO’s & Boards to create competitive advantage and achieve strategic outcomes.

Bill Jelen is the host of MrExcel.com and the author of 40 books about Microsoft Excel including Excel Gurus Gone Wild, Pivot Table Data Crunching, and Power Pivot Alchemy. He has made over 80 guest appearances on TV’s Call for Help with Leo Laporte and was voted guest of the year on the Computer America radio show. He has produced over 1800 episodes of his daily video podcast, Learn Excel from MrExcel. Before founding MrExcel.com in 1998, Bill spent twelve years as a financial analyst.

Ken Puls, FCPA, FCMA is a Chartered Professional Accountant, author, and trainer. With over 20 years of experience as a corporate controller and business owner, he has been exposed to many business systems, databases, and analysis tools, leading to a career of building Excel and Power BI-driven applications to harness data and turn it into management information.
A Microsoft Excel/Data Platform MVP since 2006 and author of 2 books, Ken has also been recognized as a Fellow of CPA Canada.

James Haight is a research analyst at Blue Hill Research focusing on analytics and emerging enterprise technologies. His primary research includes exploring the business case development and solution assessment for advanced analytics, business intelligence, and visualization applications. He also hosts Blue Hill's Emerging Tech Roundup Podcast, which features interviews with industry leaders and CEOs on the forefront of a variety of emerging technologies. Mark is an independent consultant specializing in the analysis, reporting and visualization of financial data. Over the last 20 years, he worked on many systems to measure and monitor financial performance and manage market risks that arise from banking and trading activities. He's the organizer of the London Business Analytics Group, a popular community group that holds monthly talks on topics ranging from Predictive Analytics to Power Query to Personalized Medicine. He blogs at zomalex.co.uk

Jessica is a lifelong lover of mathematics and statistics but she didn’t come to the world of computer programming until her sons began showing an interest in creating their own computer programs. She started attending classes and soon was setting them up and then teaching them herself. She is the Project Manager for Teaching Kids Programming. She is also the Director for the Center for a Healthy Lifestyle, a project of the Boys and Girls Clubs of San Dieguito.

Rick is the Cohost of Excel.TV and the Director of Business Intelligence Services at EPI-USE America Consulting. Rick combines a TDWI Certification in Business Intelligence Leadership & Management, a Six Sigma Blackbelt Certification, and 20 years of Executive/Director-Level leadership. He started his analytics and reporting career as credit risk modeler and financial analyst for Citibank in 1994. He gained extensive experience in process improvement and earned a Six Sigma Blackbelt in 2006.

Rick combines a TDWI Certification in Business Intelligence Leadership & Management, a Six Sigma Blackbelt Certification, and 20 years of Executive/Director-Level leadership. He started his analytics and reporting career as credit risk modeler and financial analyst for Citibank in 1994. He gained extensive experience in process improvement and earned a Six Sigma Blackbelt in 2006.

Avichal (Avi) Singh is a Principal Consultant at PowerPivotPro, where he has helped others transform their BI world by blogging, training, and consulting. He is currently co-authoring the 2nd edition of "DAX Formulas for PowerPivot".
Avi has personally experienced the transformation and empowerment that Power BI can bring, going from an Excel user to building large-scale Power BI platforms for 600+ users within Microsoft. His mission now is to share his knowledge about Power BI.

Jack heads growth at Chartcube, a mobile app that transforms enterprise data into an interactive "cube" you can easily explore and share with others. Previously, Jack headed growth at Prezi and Eventbrite. He is a frequent speaker on the subjects of growth hacking and software analytics.

Zack is an Excel expert consultant and co-author of ‘Excel Tables: A Complete Guide for Creating, Using, and Automating Lists and Tables’. He recently celebrated his 10th year as a Microsoft MVP for Excel and helps contribute to several online help forums. Currently he provides clients with a wide range of Office skills, including automation, add-in development (VBA and COM), template creation and specialized training. Formerly a firefighter/paramedic, he still volunteers with the ambulance.

Brandon is the Data Science Team Lead at Beyond the Arc, a Berkeley based consulting firm that helps companies use Data Science to transform the customer experience, streamline operations, and spark innovation in product development. Before joining Beyond the Arc, Brandon managed options and equities trading groups on the CBOE and American Stock Exchange. He also served as a Peace Corps volunteer for 2 years teaching English in Benin in West Africa.

Matt is a BI Professional with over 30 years’ experience in the Consumer Packaged Goods industry. He has held senior job commercial and IT roles, always leveraging data to drive success. Matt was the BI Director for Asia Pacific at The Coca-Cola Company before leaving to set up his own consulting business in 2014.
Matt is now the Principal Consultant at Excelerator BI and specialises in helping small, medium and large companies leverage Microsoft Excel, Power Pivot, Power BI and SharePoint to deliver rapid business value through Self Service Business Intelligence.

Othniel is Principal of Excellent Ones Consulting LLC. His firm provides training on finance and Microsoft Excel and creates financial models for businesses. He brings a background in finance, training, and information management systems. Prior to opening his own firm, Othniel spent 13 years in finance at various organizations. His responsibilities included building financial models, forecasting revenue, developing budgets, and analyzing data to support strategic decisions.

David Schaefer is the chief BI architect for Intel's Sales and Marketing organization where he has spent 15 years delivering enterprise business intelligence platforms and solutions for Intel's Sales and Marketing organization worldwide. He has spent 7 years directing research and development for business intelligence and analytics initiatives including self-service BI, cloud BI, in-memory analytics, data visualization, mobile BI, and applying agile principles to BI development.

Igor Peev is a Sr Program Manager on the Power Map team at Microsoft. He has worked on 3D data visualization and analysis for the last few years. His previous experience includes phone apps and media experiences.

Ken Raetz is a technology professional who has spent the past 15 years as a business intelligence and data warehouse architect, as well as a technical team manager for solutions across multiple BI platforms, including Cognos, Business Objects, and Power BI.
In 2014, Ken stepped into the brave, new world of entrepreneurship, co-founding Think Data Insights, a company focused on helping companies of all sizes effect data culture change throughout their organizations.

Greg is an Analyst leader at Intel Corporation. He has 16 years of experience in Information Technology where he has contributed as an Analyst and led several Enterprise Application programs and projects. Currently, he is the program owner for a Big Data analytics initiative called the Integrated Analytics Hub (IAH). He has led the transition of his Analyst team from traditional data warehousing method to new disruptive methods introduced by Hadoop all within one year.

Dipak is founder and CEO of Clear Analytics, a self-service BI company. He has helped design & build some of the most cutting edge business intelligence systems in the financial industry, often delivering capabilities years ahead of ‘off-the-shelf’ products at the time. Dipak's unique background in art + design helps him to deliver complex system workflows and Business Intelligence solutions into a simple and user friendly solution that result in exceptional rates of user adoption.

Minnie is a business development manager at Clear Analytics, an excel based business intelligence platform. She has worked in various financial technology firms to help international institutions increase their efficiency in the tough regulatory environment.

Jeff is a Finance Director at Microsoft, which he joined in 2000. In his work with Enterprise Services, Jeff makes extensive use of Microsoft’s BI tools to analyze sales trends and educate business partners and stakeholders. He a regular presenter at the Executive Briefing Center and has made a number of trips to work directly with Microsoft customers in building out their own analytics. An avid traveler, Jeff has lived in Kazakhstan, Singapore and Germany.

Satheesh Iyer is a Product Manager in HP’s Enterprise Group and focuses on Big Data and Microsoft Analytics Platform Systems . Satheesh has over 20 years technology industry experience, and with varied backgrounds in enterprise systems and solutions, Big Data IT, database technologies, solution architecture and data security.

Santhosh is a Business analytics delivery lead at Tiger analytics with 5+ years of experience working in Analytics Stat-ups. Prior experience includes working in a variety of verticals including Social Media, F&B, e-Commerce and Payments. He helps in providing client specific support including dashboards, custom insights, scorecards and ad-hoc data science requests
